            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>Now here's where the UI magic happens. LiveProgressSink implements RuntimeEventSink and sits in the session's composite sink. It receives every RuntimeEvent for that request and translates them into SSE JSON. A router_decision event becomes a route_decision SSE message with label, why, and confidence. A worker_agent_started becomes a worker_start with task title and doc scope. Internally it uses a thread-safe queue — when the request finishes, we push None as a terminator. The SSE generator reads off the queue and formats as 'data: {json}' until it sees None. So the client sees real-time updates like 'Planning tasks' → 'Dispatching workers' → 'Worker 1: analyzing contracts' → 'Final synthesis complete' without any polling. Events not in our phase labels are either handled specifically or dropped to avoid noise.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
